      <description>&lt;div&gt;Supposedly the Time cleric hammer(Theoretically all Cleric &amp;quot;gods&amp;quot; hammers) has a proc rate mod of 630%, and Panther has a proc rate mod of 400% to give you an idea as to how often that fires.  So if I can drop 1475 mana on three dual weilding melee, and get even one proc per dual weilder per tick, I'm doing 1200 Chromatic -300 DPS from Panther.  With DoTs, I'm spending 1648 for 1121 DR/PR/MR -0  damage per tick.  DoT's aren't even the most efficient shaman DPS anymore.  To be perfectly honest, I'd rather have Panther cleared to work on pets than to have the DoT's repaired.  I'm getting more and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;more efficient&lt;/em&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;DPS from one spell cast repeatedly at zero agro than having 4 or 5 up so I can debuff and cast less than 200 DPS of DoTs in an age with melee putting out 1000 DPS.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
