      <description>&lt;div&gt;Uh... yeah but the buff proc has an innately coded 400 rate mod.  So it goes off about a 2/3 as often as a cleric hammer.  And as a warrior who tanked a lot of Sebilis I'm acutely aware of how often those things go off and how much I'd kill being able to swing two of them :p  But that was the point I was getting at.  Panther fires off about 2/3 as often as a cleric hammer and those things are always going off.  That the chance of each melee being able to get at least one proc per tick, let alone one proc per round was inherently high and likely.  So even &amp;quot;worst case&amp;quot; the DPS from 3 casts of Panther was more effective and more efficient than stacking our three highest level DoT's.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
